post_text: The Mine Hill Teacher's Association is accepting applications for their annual scholarships given out to high school seniors that will be moving on to a two or four year college in the fall. In order to be eligible the applicant must have graduated and attended Canfield Avenue School for a minimum of four years, perform scholastically in the top third of their class, possess good character, and be an active participant in their school and community. Applications can be downloaded online at www.minehillcas.org under the announcement section and the deadline to submit applications is Friday, April 3, 2020.

post_text: Trout Update! Our fish are starting to hatch!!
text: Trout Update! Our fish are starting to hatch!!

post_text:
New addition to the CAS "family" - This year CAS is participating in an exciting program called Trout in the Classroom. Schools throughout the United States participate in this program and receive different types of trout depending on what is native to their area. Schools throughout New Jersey received their trout eggs last week (mostly rainbow and brook trout).

In the science lab, there is a 55 gallon fish tank set up including a chiller to keep the water at the 52‚Å∞ F (the ideal temperature for trout). In the tank there are currently trout eggs in the breeder box and a few have hatched! The hatchlings are called alevins and will remain at this stage for about 14 ‚Äì 30 days. At this stage, they mostly lie on their sides, getting nutrients from their yolk sacs while they grow. There is a great trout life cycle chart located in front of the tank. The trout will be with us until late May or early June at which time we will be releasing them into a local river.

post_text: In late November, Mrs. Champagne's class began a cross-curricular, multi-week unit on Gingerbread. This unit incorporated Math (topics included: geometric concepts, budgeting, and engineering concepts, etc.), ELA (informational text, comparing stories, and writing in response to a life experience, etc.), and Science (engineering concepts, changes in form, etc.). During this unit, her class entered a structure into the Frelinghuysen Arboretum's Gingerbread Wonderland. The unit ended with a field trip to visit the Gingerbread Wonderland Display. This is an annual event at the Arboretum and the general public is invited to vote on their favorite entries in various categories. Imagine the excitement when CAS was informed that Mrs.Champagne's class won first place in the school category!
